        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Slave-Free Business Certification Act of 202</b><strong>2</strong><br> <br> This bill requires businesses with annual revenue greater than $500 million to audit their supply chains for labor practices or human trafficking activities that violate specified national or international standards and report the results to the Department of Labor.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
